  "Vonage SMS API Documentation": "",
  "Vonage SMS enables text message notifications for ChurchCRM using the Vonage API (formerly Nexmo). Send SMS alerts to parents when their child checks in via the kiosk system.": "",
  "Vonage charges per SMS sent. Pricing varies by destination country. See the Vonage pricing page for current rates. New accounts receive free trial credit for testing.": "",
  "What Gets Tracked": "",
  "When MailChimp is configured, a 'MailChimp' tab appears on Person view pages showing:\n\n- Email subscription status across all lists\n- Which lists the person is subscribed to\n- Subscription statistics": "",
  "When a member doesn't have an uploaded photo, ChurchCRM checks if they have a Gravatar associated with their email address. If a Gravatar exists, it displays that image. If not, the configured default image style is used.": "",
  "When auto-backup is enabled (interval > 0 hours), ChurchCRM will automatically create and upload a full database backup at the specified interval. The backup runs as part of normal page loads, so the system must have regular user activity to trigger backups.\n\nRecommended intervals:\n- Daily backup: 24 hours\n- Twice daily: 12 hours\n- Weekly: 168 hours": "",
  "When enabled and configured, ChurchCRM sends alert messages to your OpenLP server using the API v2 endpoint (POST /api/v2/plugins/alerts). These alerts appear as overlay notifications on your projected display.": "",
  "When enabled, hides the address field for people not assigned to a family": "",
  "When enabled, hides the latitude/longitude fields in the Family Editor. Geocoding still runs in the background.": "",
  "You can also trigger a manual backup at any time:\n1. Go to the External Backup settings page (Plugins > External Backup)\n2. Select backup type (Database Only or Full Backup)\n3. Click 'Backup to WebDAV Now'\n\nDatabase Only backups are smaller and faster. Full backups include uploaded photos.": "",
